attachments.title: Whose side are you on? Separate lawyers defend Trump, aides
attachments.text: WASHINGTON (AP) — As the government's Russia investigations heat up, a growing cast of lawyers is signing up to defend President Donald Trump and his associates. But the interests
attachments.fallback: AP News: Whose side are you on? Separate lawyers defend Trump, aides

text: "Trump himself has both an outside legal team and a new in-house special counsel, Ty Cobb, for Russia-related matters."

Also this, in the Life Comes At You Pretty Fast department:

"Michael Caputo, another former campaign aide, met with House lawmakers last week and says he expects to testify again in front of senators and potentially Mueller’s team. Caputo is being represented by former New York State Attorney General Dennis Vacco, and said he’s liquidating his children’s college funds to pay the bills.

Asked about the campaign money covering Don Jr. and other folks’ legal fees, he responded: “Lucky for them. And unlucky for me. And unlucky for my children who are now going to community college.”
